I was lazy 
I was overweight 
I was unmotivated 
I was comfortable 
I was selfish 

Since my brain injury, I am a complete different person. I care more about what and whose around me than just myself. I care about what I put out to the world. I do not care what people think of me, if you don‚Äôt like me, well YOUR LOSS BECAUSE IM A BAD ASS BITCH! I have a better and healthier relationship with food and have actually researched what I put into my body. (I say this now, but tomorrow is my birthday party, and I asked everyone to bring baked goods.. MODERATION?!) 

I‚Äôm proud of the person I am today, nor am I ashamed of who I was. I have grown and educated myself. My routine isn‚Äôt autopilot mode anymore. I challenge myself everyday, I encourage you to do the same. 

I admit, after I got discharged as an outpatient, I would wake up.. watch tv, and not do so much for my emotional, physical and mental health. 

It‚Äôs hard not to mourn your old self. Create yourself again! This is the time to change for the better and learn about yourself! 
